            <h2 class="element-invisible">You are here</h2><ul class="breadcrumb"><li><a href="/front">Home</a></li></ul>      <a id="main-content"></a>
                    <h1>About Sound On Sound</h1>
                                          <article id="node-4912555" class="node node--page node--full node--page--full clearfix" about="/about-sos" typeof="foaf:Document" role="article" class="node node--page node--full node--page--full">
      
  <div class="node--content-wrapper">
    <div class="node--inner-wrapper">
    
      
    <span property="dc:title" content="About Sound On Sound" class="rdf-meta element-hidden"></span>
    
    <div  class="node__content">
	  
  <div class="field--body">
    <h2><span class="media-image-header"><a href="https://dt7v1i9vyp3mf.cloudfront.net/styles/news_large/s3/imagelibrary/m/may_2024_bundle3-5UiS8OiGrQiIK.h0FQf7pNWT8ctOsh7o.jpg" title="" class="colorbox" data-colorbox-gallery="all" data-cbox-img-attrs="{&quot;title&quot;: &quot;May 2024 Print+Digital Issue&quot;, &quot;alt&quot;: &quot;May 2024 Print+Digital Issue&quot;}"><img typeof="foaf:Image" src="https://dt7v1i9vyp3mf.cloudfront.net/styles/header/s3/imagelibrary/m/may_2024_bundle3-vMrjw_ojyz_WKGY3OAfX8Xdm1.LVSJB8.jpg" width="620" height="286" alt="May 2024 Print+Digital Issue" title="May 2024 Print+Digital Issue" /></a><span class="caption" style="width:620px;">May 2024 Print+Digital Issue</span></span></h2>

<h2><a href="/shop/subscriptions" target="_blank">Print</a> • <a href="/magazine" target="_blank">Online</a> • <a href="/information/tablet-smartphone-app-faq" target="_blank">Tablet | Mobile App</a>&nbsp;•&nbsp;<a href="/information/how-buy-access-sos-full-issue-pdfs" target="_blank">Full-Issue PDF</a>&nbsp;• <a href="https://www.youtube.com/user/soundonsoundvideo" target="_blank">Videos</a> • <a href="/sos-podcasts" target="_blank">Podcasts</a></h2>

<p><strong>Welcome to <em>Sound On Sound</em>, the world's premier audio&nbsp;recording technology magazine.</strong></p>

<p>Based in Cambridge, England and independently-owned, we've been delivering our high-quality <em>Sound On Sound</em> print magazine every month since 1985. In 1998 we launched our first website and in 2012 our iPad digital edition app received great praise and endorsements from our global readership. The current website houses our continually-expanding archive of authoritative and highly-respected articles, news and up to the minute in-depth reviews (16,805 so far) that chart the impact of technology on the music production and recording processes.</p>

<h2>The Trusted Resource For All Things Audio</h2>

<p class="nindent"><em>Sound On Sound</em> is known for its thorough and unbiased reviews of music technology products, such as audio interfaces, microphones, and software. It also features articles on recording techniques, music production and sound engineering, as well as insightful interviews with musicians, producers, and mix engineers.</p>

<p><em>Sound On Sound</em> is highly respected globally due to its reputation for high-quality content and its consistent focus on providing detailed, technical information to its readers. The magazine and website have a strong following among music professionals and enthusiasts across the world, and its articles and reviews are often cited as authoritative sources within the industry and education.</p>

<p>Every month, our UK/EU/World and North America print magazines and digital editions deliver consistently more pages than any competing title, packed full of in-depth product tests of:</p>

<ul>
	<li><a href="/recorders?f%5B0%5D=node%253Afield_section%3A6970" target="_blank"><strong>Recording Systems</strong></a></li>
	<li><strong><a href="/computer-software" target="_blank">Music Software</a>: <a href="/daws" target="_blank">DAWs</a>, <a href="/computer-software/virtual-instrument?f%5B0%5D=node%253Afield_section%3A6970" target="_blank">Virtual Instruments</a>, <a href="/plug-ins?f%5B0%5D=node%253Afield_section%3A6970" target="_blank">Plug-ins</a></strong></li>
	<li><a href="/audio-interfaces" target="_blank"><strong>Audio Interfaces</strong></a></li>
	<li><strong><a href="/synthesizers" target="_blank">Synthesizers</a>, <a href="/keyboards" target="_blank">Keyboards</a>, <a href="/synthesizers?f%5B0%5D=node%253Afield_section%3A6970&amp;f%5B1%5D=node%253Afield_hardware_format%3A8500" target="_blank">Eurorack Modules</a></strong></li>
	<li><a href="/signal-processors" target="_blank"><strong>Effects &amp; Outboard Processors</strong></a></li>
	<li><a href="/microphones-miking?f%5B0%5D=node%253Afield_section%3A6970" target="_blank"><strong>Microphones</strong></a></li>
	<li><a href="/preamps-channel-strips" target="_blank"><strong>Preamps &amp; Channel Strips</strong></a></li>
	<li><a href="/mixers?f%5B0%5D=node%253Afield_section%3A6970" target="_blank"><strong style="font-family: 'Open Sans';">Mixers</strong></a></li>
	<li><strong style="font-family: 'Open Sans';"><a href="/drum-machines" target="_blank">Drum Machines</a> <a href="/sequencers-grooveboxes" target="_blank">&amp; Grooveboxes</a></strong></li>
	<li><a href="/controllers" target="_blank"><strong style="font-family: 'Open Sans';">MIDI Controllers</strong></a></li>
	<li><strong><a href="/monitors-monitoring" target="_blank">Monitor Speakers, </a><a href="/monitors-monitoring/headphones" target="_blank">Headphones &amp;</a> <a href="/monitors-monitoring/monitor-controller" target="_blank">Monitor Controllers</a></strong></li>
	<li><a href="/pa-live-sound?f%5B0%5D=node%253Afield_section%3A6970" target="_blank"><strong>PA / Live Sound systems</strong></a></li>
	<li><a href="/search/all?terms=mac%20windows%20computer" target="_blank"><strong>Music Computers / Tablets</strong></a></li>
	<li><strong><a href="/samplers-sampling" target="_blank">Samplers &amp;</a> <a href="/sample-libraries" target="_blank">Sample Libraries</a></strong></li>
	<li>And much more!</li>
</ul>

<p>Plus the most insightful <strong>Musician</strong>/&nbsp;<strong>Mix Engineer</strong>/&nbsp;<strong>Record Producer interviews</strong> you'll read anywhere. Our regular <strong>Tutorials</strong> and practical 'how to' <strong>Masterclasses</strong> offer direct, no-nonsense advice, to help you gain the most from your studio tools — whatever your level of expertise.</p>

<p><em>Sound On Sound</em> is recognised internationally as the 'bible' of the music recording industry and a&nbsp;firm favourite of top record producers, mixing/sound engineers and recording artists. <strong><a href="/people/happy-25th-birthday-sound-sound" target="_blank">Check out these fabulous industry reader endorsements</a></strong> — all volunteered openly and we didn't pay anyone!</p>

<h2>Sound On Sound - "The Independent Voice Of Music Technology"</h2>

<p><span class="media-image-left"><a href="https://dt7v1i9vyp3mf.cloudfront.net/styles/news_large/s3/imagelibrary/s/sos1985firstissue-kqvL8rjOR11J01BjtPb4JfDGrzYayH0q.gif" title="" class="colorbox" data-colorbox-gallery="all" data-cbox-img-attrs="{&quot;title&quot;: &quot;SOS&#039;s first issue featured Midge Ure and went on sale mid-October 1985, with a November cover date.&quot;, &quot;alt&quot;: &quot;SOS&#039;s first issue featured Midge Ure and went on sale mid-October 1985, with a November cover date.&quot;}"><img typeof="foaf:Image" src="https://dt7v1i9vyp3mf.cloudfront.net/styles/news_preview/s3/imagelibrary/s/sos1985firstissue-vojPRIk7uN1WN2yXDkK3EC9TSud6vB6T.gif" width="165" height="218" alt="SOS&#039;s first issue featured Midge Ure and went on sale mid-October 1985, with a November cover date." title="SOS&#039;s first issue featured Midge Ure and went on sale mid-October 1985, with a November cover date." /></a><span class="caption" style="width:165px;">SOS's first issue featured Midge Ure and went on sale mid-October 1985, with a November cover date.</span></span></p>

<p><em>Sound On Sound</em> has consistently remained at the forefront of music recording technology since it was first&nbsp;launched in October 1985 by the visionary SOS Publications Group with national TV advertisements on the UK's top Channel&nbsp;4 TV music show, <em>The Tube</em>.</p>

<p>For over 38 years now, we've been championing the convergence of music software, MIDI, computer technology and audio recording equipment that continues to revolutionise the audio production market today.</p>

<p><em>With undoubtedly the most experienced editorial team to grace any music magazine's staff list, our editorial integrity and professional reputation are highly-prized and internationally respected by both our global readership and advertisers alike.</em></p>

<p>So browse our award-winning web site, <a href="/search" target="_blank"><strong>search our extensive archive of over 16,805 past articles</strong></a> or swap helpful hints/ tips/ hacks and chew the proverbial fat with fellow project studio enthusiasts and audio experts in the ever-popular <strong><a href="/forum">SOS Forum</a></strong>. Then you will discover why Sound On Sound remains the "yardstick by which all other music recording magazines are measured" <em>[Chicago Tribune newspaper]</em>.</p>

<ul>
	<li>For early SOS issues published between 1985&nbsp;-&nbsp;1993, which are not yet available on this web site, please visit <a href="http://www.muzines.co.uk/list_issues.php?id=5" target="_blank">Mu:zines — the Music Magazine Archive</a>.</li>
</ul>

<h2>GET A FREE COPY</h2>

<ul>
	<li>Never seen a copy of <em>Sound On Sound</em> Print magazine? In 2018, SOS began marketing a&nbsp;downloadable <a href="/shop/article-pdf" target="_blank"><strong>FULL&nbsp;ISSUE&nbsp;PDF</strong></a> for anyone, anywhere in the world, who wants quick and convenient offline access to a full&nbsp;magazine complete with all its advertisement pages.</li>
	<li>Alternatively, sign up for our browser-based Replica Magazine which we are making freely available. Visit <a href="/digital-magazine" target="_blank">www.soundonsound.com/digital-magazine</a></li>
</ul>

